The evidence with the title 'Key facts about the uninsured population | the Henry J. Kaiser ... ' says Sep 19, 2017  ... Most uninsured people are in low - income families and have at least one worker in the family.Reflecting the more limited availability of public coverage in some states, adults are more likely to be uninsured than children. People of color are at higher risk of being uninsured than non-Hispanic Whites. 
